caption.body: Britain's former international flag carrier airline, British Overseas Airways Corporation, or BOAC was founded by an Act of the British Parliament #onthisday in 1939. The company was created as a merger of Imperial Airways and British Airways Ltd. In 1974, BOAC merged with British European Airways (BEA) to form British Airways, Britainâ€™s current flag carrier. Did you ever fly on BOAC?   Image: BOAC (British Overseas Airways Corporation) postcard, (reproduction of c. 1950 poster) Great Britain, 1970s. Gift of Captain Jon Simmonds. 2015.057.223
